by Synne Industries » Tue Feb 16, 2021 12:16 pm

You see a whole lot more nations these days with some mention of ideology or general functioning system as part of the name, usually in the form of (ideology)ian (country). I’ve only been around for just under two years now so I could be completely wrong but that’s how I’ve seen the trend going recently. These nations fall into the pit of being too fixated on whatever their ideology is and what it does or what their country does because of it while everything else is either absent or bland. I understand that Nationstates is a politically focused Australian browser game but seeing whateverism take center stage instead of anything else part of a nation 4 times out of 5 really drains from the overall experience, especially on F7. Militaries can also fall victim to this but considering the how and the why people do these things, it’s a whole realm of its own.
